%I A395622 #23 Jun 16 2026 20:52:29
%S A395622 5,6,8,11,17,23,31,73,108,123,219,306,399,548,765,870,925,2253
%N A395622 Nonsquare integers c > 0 for which there are positive nonsquare integers a < b < c such that sqrt(a) + sqrt(b) + sqrt(c) is closer to an integer than for all smaller nonsquare c > b > a > 0.
%C A395622 It is not necessary to know the "best" a- and b-values for a given a(n) = c, as long as it satisfies the given condition for *all* smaller c > b > a > 0; i.e., in particular for all triples having a(n-1) as largest member. But to extend the sequence further and ensure the next candidate for a(n+1) meets the condition, one has to either find the triple (a, b, a(n)) that minimizes the distance of the sum from the nearest integer, or use some other reasoning involving bounds or estimates to make sure that there is no triple involving the smaller a(n) which yields a smaller distance than a(n+1).
%e A395622 The smallest triple of distinct positive nonsquare integers is (a,b,c) = (2,3,5), for which the sum of square roots is 5.38... at distance 0.38... from the nearest integer, so a(1) = 5.
%e A395622 For (a,b,c) = (2,5,6) the sum of square roots is ~ 6.0998 at distance ~ 0.0998 from the nearest integer 6, so a(2) = 6.
%e A395622 For (a,b,c) = (3,6,8) the sum of square roots is ~ 7.00997 at distance ~ 0.00997 from the nearest integer 7, so a(3) = 8.
%e A395622 For (a,b,c) = (5,6,11) the sum of square roots is ~ 8.002 at distance ~ 0.002 from the nearest integer 8, so a(4) = 11.
%o A395622 (PARI) A395622_upto(N=oo, start=1, d=oo) = {for(a=1,N, my(sa=sqrt(a)); issquare(a)|| for(b=2,a-1, my(sab=sa+sqrt(b)); issquare(b)|| forstep(c=a-1,b+1,-1, issquare(c)|| if(my(t=sqrt(c)+sab)|| abs(t-=t\/1)<d, d=abs(t); sa==sqrt(a)&& print1(a", ");sa+=1))))} \\ The optional start value allows to extend the sequence from a given starting point. For example, A395622_upto(,765) will yield the subsequent terms 870, 925, ... The optional 3rd argument allows to exclude solutions that are at a distance > the specified d-value.
%Y A395622 Cf. A395621 (similar for just two numbers).
%K A395622 nonn,hard,more,changed
%O A395622 1,1
%A A395622 _M. F. Hasler_, May 29 2026
%E A395622 a(16)-a(18) from _Sean A. Irvine_, Jun 02 2026
